==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intractable
<hw>In*tract"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intractabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>intraitable</ets>, formerly also
<ets>intractable</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Tractable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not tractable; not easily governed,
managed, or directed; indisposed to be taught, disciplined, or tamed;
violent; stubborn; obstinate; refractory; <as>as, an
<ex>intractable</ex> child</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Stubborn; perverse; obstinate; refractory; cross;
unmanageable; unruly; headstrong; violent; ungovernable;
unteachable.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*tract"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*tract"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intractile</ent>⟦br⟧
